\pard\f0\fs28  {\b G. byzantinus} Baker, {\i Gard. Chron.} ser. 3, {\b 13}: 226 (1893), which differs only in the presence of a distinct green patch at the base of each inner perianth-segment, and sometimes in being less robust, has been reported from Turkey-in-Europe, but apparently in error. It is native to N.W. Anatolia, and is probably best treated as a subspecies of {\b 2}.
