\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. martinezii} Lag.,{\i  Gen. Sp. Nov.} 14 (1816). Bulb up to 5 cm in diameter. Leaves up to 25 cm × 10 mm, appearing after anthesis, broadly linear, with a longitudinal pale band on upper surface. Scape up to 20 cm. Spathe 15-30 mm; pedicels 10-20 mm. Perianth-segments 8-12 mm, white, with a green stripe on outer surface, patent at anthesis, erect and persistent in fruit. Capsule 7-12 mm in diameter; seeds c. 5 mm, black. Flowering in late summer. 2n = 22.{\i  Crevices of calcareous rocks. S. & S.E. Spain.} Hs.
